Overview
--------

A DKMS module that builds and installs legacy DRM drivers.

Requirements
------------

* dkms
* Current kernel source
* Configured header path for kernel kernel

Installation
------------

* Copy files to /usr/src/drm_legacy-0.1/
* dkms add drm_legacy/0.1
* dkms autoinstall drm_legacy/0.1

A Word of Warning
-----------------

CONFIG_DRM_LEGACY was created because the interfaces pose many
security problems. The drivers covered by this config option are
likely to be poorly maintained.
